Bug Report 1 

Bug ID: BR-AUTH-001 

Title/Summary: Registration allows creating an account with a 1-character password 

Module/Area: Signup → Enter Account Information 

URL: https://automationexercise.com/signup 

Environment: macOS Tahoe 26.2, Chrome Version 147.0.7727.102 (Official Build) (arm64) 

Severity: Major (Security / account protection risk) 

Priority: Medium 

Reproducibility: Always 

  

Preconditions: 

  

User has started signup from Signup / Login page and is on “Enter Account Information”. 

Steps to reproduce: 

  

Open Signup / Login page. 

Enter a name and a unique email address. 

Click Signup. 

On Enter Account Information page, enter a password consisting of 1 character. 

Fill all mandatory Address Information fields with valid values. 

Click Create Account. 

Expected result: 

  

The system should enforce a minimum password length (commonly 6–8+ characters) and show a validation message, preventing account creation. 

Actual result: 

  

The system allows a 1-character password and proceeds with account creation. 

  

Related test case: TC-AUTH-011 (your suite) 

Notes: 

  

Even if requirements are not documented, allowing extremely short passwords is a common security weakness and typically treated as a defect or at least a security improvement. 

Bug Report 2 

Bug ID: BR-AUTH-002 

Title/Summary: Mobile Number field accepts letters and special characters during registration 

Module/Area: Signup → Address Information 

URL: https://automationexercise.com/signup 

Environment: macOS Tahoe 26.2, Chrome Version 147.0.7727.102 (Official Build) (arm64) 

Severity: Major (Data integrity issue if account can be created with invalid phone) 

Priority: Medium 

Reproducibility: Always 

  

Preconditions: 

  

User is on “Enter Account Information” page during signup. 

Steps to reproduce: 

  

Start signup with a unique email and open Enter Account Information page. 

Fill all required fields with valid values. 

In Mobile Number enter ABC-123 or !!!@@@. 

Click Create Account. 

Expected result: 

  

The system should validate the mobile number format and prevent submission with non-phone characters (allow only digits and optionally +, spaces, hyphens, parentheses). 

Actual result: 

  

The system accepts letters and special characters in Mobile Number and does not show validation error. 

Related test case: TC-AUTH-019 (your suite) 

Notes: 

If the application is intended to accept any text in this field (unlikely), then field should be labeled differently (e.g., “Contact information”) or validation rules should be clarified. 

Bug Report 3 

Bug ID: BR-AUTH-003 

Title/Summary: Zipcode field accepts alphabetic characters (no format validation) 

Module/Area: Signup → Address Information 

URL: https://automationexercise.com/signup 

Environment: macOS Tahoe 26.2, Chrome Version 147.0.7727.102 (Official Build) (arm64) 

Severity: Minor to Major (depends on business rules; typically Minor/Medium) 

Priority: Low/Medium 

Reproducibility: Always 

  

Preconditions: 

  

User is on “Enter Account Information” page during signup. 

Steps to reproduce: 

  

Start signup and open Enter Account Information page. 

Fill all required fields with valid values. 

In Zipcode enter ABCDE (letters only). 

Click Create Account. 

Expected result: 

The system should validate the zipcode format according to selected country (commonly numeric; at least should reject pure letters where not applicable) OR clearly allow alphanumeric zipcodes based on country rules. 

Actual result: 

 The system accepts letters in Zipcode and does not show validation error.  

Related test case: TC-AUTH-018 (your suite) 

Notes: 

 Some countries have alphanumeric postal codes, so proper expected behavior should be based on the selected country. If country is India (as in screenshot), typically numeric pincode is expected. 

